\pard\sa180\sl276\slmult1\b World Soaring Cup\b0\par

\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs28\b\cf2 Data source\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
SoaringSpot MCP, contest 5249 \endash  \i 40th FAI World Gliding Championships\i0 , Cz\'eastochowa-Rudniki, Poland, 16\endash 30 May 2026. The MCP credentials are scoped to this single contest (client ID prefix 5249_), which is the WGC of the current championship calendar year. Three classes were flown, each with 10 official tasks.\par

\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs28\b\cf2 Method\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
For each class champion:\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f1\fs20 ratio = champion's final score \'f7 maximum possible score\f0\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
where \b maximum possible score\b0  = the sum, over the 10 official tasks, of each day's top (day-winner's) points \endash  i.e. the maximum points available each day after devaluation. The pilot with the highest ratio across all world-champion classes wins.\par

