\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs28\b\cf2 Winner\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
\b Victor Mallick (France) \endash  18 Metre Class\b0  is the IGC Champion Pilot of the Year and takes the World Soaring Cup, with a ratio of \b 0.9545 (95.45%)\b0  of the maximum possible score \endash  the highest among all three world champions.\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1
Although Levin's Open total (8945) was the highest raw score, the Open class had a higher achievable maximum (9517, since 8 of 10 days were valued at the full 1000 points), so his percentage of the maximum was the lowest of the three.\par

\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs28\b\cf2 Caveat\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf3
These are the only World-Championship classes reachable through the supplied MCP credentials. If other WGCs were held elsewhere in 2026 (e.g. Club / Standard / 15 m / Women's / Junior), each would need its own per-competition credentials to be included in the comparison.\cf1\par

